                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                        <locus target="#3v #38v #42r #109r" facs="005 040 043 110"/>, etc., words of text are written interlinearly;
                        <locus target="#6v #11v #12r #15r" facs="008 013 016"/>, etc., lines of text are written interlinearly;
                        <locus target="#10v #34v #35r #42v #48v #59r" facs="012 036 044 050 060"/>, etc., erasure markings are visible;
                        <locus target="#20r #35v #44r #97r" facs="021 037 045 098"/>, e.g., text has been removed.
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                      appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                      completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to
                      avoid having to go onto the next line, e.g., <locus target="#8r #19r #25v" facs="009 020 027"/>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
